##Mall operators and tenants join hands to save themselves

Industry self-help, to ensure the stability of business, to carry out the epidemic.

Starting on the eve of the Lunar New Year, the shopping malls under the Red Star Macalline, a leading household brand, have closed for the holiday. But the outbreak has pushed back their opening date.

The Red Star Macalline had originally planned to resume operations on Jan. 29, but as the situation became more serious, the opening date was first postponed until Feb. 15, and the latest announcement was tentatively scheduled for Feb. 29.

Affected by the epidemic is not only home shopping malls, even if the normal opening of large-scale shopping malls, the flow of people is also sharply reduced.

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, pedestrians in Shenzhen's China Resources Vientiane City stroll around wearing masks, restaurants are empty, and many people in fashion shops are enthusiastically choosing clothes. By February 3, Vientiane City began to shorten business hours, and many shops even directly choose short-term closure.

Since the Spring Festival, more and more shopping centers have chosen to shorten their business hours, even calling in the official slogan: Staying at home is safer.

Under the impact of the epidemic, the pause button was not only the city's busy traffic, but also the crowds in shopping malls. Almost all shopping centers saw a sharp drop in passenger flow and sales during the 2020 Spring Festival, according to the report on the shopping center industry's special investigation to combat the epidemic released by the Commercial Real Estate Working Committee of the all-union Real Estate Chamber.

"Rent Reduction" has become an important way for most commercial real estate operators to cope with the difficult times together with merchants. "Rent Reduction" , commercial real estate operators are also thinking about how to save themselves, some take advantage of the development of online business, some principles to wait for the end of the epidemic, trying to deal with the epidemic after the resumption of work.

###Self-help and leverage

Liu Jiang has been on China's Home Education Platform, listening to the two-day course, learning is "in half a year to seize the annual performance as a home owner to win the 'war' six-pronged sword. "

He runs a home furnishing store opening time is uncertain, worried about future performance, he would like to listen to the marketing teacher taught method.

The course is offered free of charge by the Red Star Macalline. China's largest home furnishing store operator announced on February 4 that it would open its "China Home Education Platform" free of charge, hoping to take advantage of the market's current downturn and give industry practitioners a chance to learn about the subject.

Earlier, on February 2, to mitigate tenants'losses, the Red Star Macalline announced that it would waive the rent and management fees for any month in 2020 for the relevant tenants of the 82 eligible self-service shopping malls. The amount of rent reduction exceeds 500 million yuan.

Zhu Jiagui, chief executive officer and general manager of Red Star Macalline, told interface news, "since January 28, before the official announcement, we have been discussing rent reduction and follow-up measures to deal with the epidemic in the hope that we can join forces upstream, midstream and downstream of the industry to combat the epidemic. "

In addition to the rent reduction measures for the self-operated shopping malls, the Red Star Macalline also communicates with its partners who entrust the management of the shopping malls, hoping that the partners will also come up with a "rent reduction" policy to ease the pressure on the businesses.

"judging from the feedback so far, most of the partners can understand and are willing to support the rent reduction policy. We will disclose the details later, " Zhu said.

Red Star Macalline calls for upstream factories and brands to help the dealers accordingly, forming a 1 + 1 + 1 model to carry through three difficult months together. In particular, "stores pay a month's rent, factories pay a month's salary, and dealers pay a month's salary. Together, we can fight the epidemic for 100 days and the market will be very stable. "

As of February 12,200 home brand enterprises have participated in the support policy for distributors, ranging from those that reduce the ex-factory price of their products to those that choose to undertake a month's salary for national distributors...

For some businesses facing cash flow constraints, the Red Star Macalline is also giving corresponding support from the financing side. Their supply chain finance platform, in cooperation with the Shanghai branch of the Agricultural Bank of China and the Shanghai Branch of the Bank of Shanghai, has long provided preferential interest rate credit support to Red Star Macalline merchants, the total amount of small business loans granted to merchants amounted to 2.5 billion yuan.

In addition, Red Star Macalline has joined forces with Alibaba, Ant Financial and e commerce banks to provide merchants with all-round support, including online sales support, merchants'financing support and interest rate concessions, among them, the online commercial bank provided 1.5 billion capital in response to the outbreak to eligible merchants to provide liquidity support. Alibaba is the third-largest shareholder in 601828.Sh  .

"It is very difficult for all industries now. For us, we must first help the industry to save itself, ensure its stable operation and survive the epidemic. When the epidemic is over, we believe that the industry will surely enjoy explosive growth, " Zhu said.

In addition to self-help, Red Star Meikai is also taking advantage of the development of online business. "In the past, many distributors did not have the motivation to develop their online business, but now because of the epidemic, they have realized the importance of online business and are more active in cooperating with us. "

According to Zhu, from February 3 to February 23,2020, their soft-fitting furniture supply chain platform "design cloud" has been open to all the Red Star Macalline, free of charge to provide 2 months of cloud design software unlimited rendering capabilities. Cloud services are designed in 3d to provide the ability to create solutions online and communicate remotely.

The Red Star Macalline also announced that it will be available free of charge to the entire home improvement and home furnishing industry from February 10 to April 10 to help businesses take full advantage of online marketing tools.

In May last year, after Alibaba bought a stake in Red Star Macalline, the company launched tmall Tongcheng, a flagship store for local home building materials, centered on Shanghai and Nanjing.

Affected by the outbreak, Zhu said, "in 2020, the Red Star Macalline will set up cross-city stations covering the whole country, and now the number of merchants applying to join the cross-city stations is increasing. "

Similar to some real estate companies that want to learn from Li Jiaqi's live broadcast of selling real estate, Red Star Macalline also plans to train mall guides, hoping that they will also become internet celebrities who bring goods to home stores.

Shopping malls, which used to invest little in "online business" , are now trying to lure merchants online.

Shenzhen Haiya riotous city, Zhuoyuehui, Xinghe cocopark and other shopping malls in the official Wechat Push, while promoting shops, but also to join the mall guide Wechat Qr Code, said can be "no contact distribution" ; In Shenzhen, the company name of Vientiane Tiandi updates the list of takeout vendors that can be delivered "contactless" ; in Shenzhen, the company name of Zhuoyue Center is embedded with brand names and small programs; and in Tianhong Department Store, it promotes its own small programs. Calling for online shopping... .

"self-help is definitely our primary goal. Besides this, we also hope the country will introduce supportive policies to support us in tax, fiscal, financial and other areas to tide us over the difficult times, " Zhu said.

Knight Frank, a real estate consultancy, expects that in addition to owners'incentives for retailers, the government and financial institutions may introduce supportive policies in areas such as tax cuts, increased currency liquidity and loan rollover, to help these companies get through this.

With the help of "online" self-help, no matter how effective, commercial real estate operators are facing a special period of few ways.

Commercial real estate operators will face more pressure to prevent the epidemic as work resumes in an orderly manner.

###Test of prevention and control after resuming work

"orders are probably 98 percent lower than usual. The main job of the day is not to make milk tea, but to sterilize the shops every hour, and the store staff will come to check it every day, " said Nai Xue, a tea worker at a shopping mall in Futian, Shenzhen.

The epidemic has made regular disinfection standard in shopping malls.

Cade Group has asked the national projects to start the emergency process, do a good job in the epidemic prevention measures.

According to Khed, a series of preventive measures have been carried out in the shopping mall, including organizing relevant personnel training, elimination of public areas, cleaning of air conditioning filters, heat screening, setting up isolation rooms and so on, and prepared a mask, first aid kit, protective clothing, temperature gun, disposable gloves and other emergency medical supplies, to ensure the safety and health of the consumer environment.

Based on guidelines from the WHO and the infectious disease, cade has developed a set of prevention and control protocols and procedures for public places. Take the isolation room for example, the process is detailed to the isolation room location, room size, ventilation mode, room signs and supporting facilities, personnel access requirements, and detailed check list to ensure that the measures in place.

Some of cade's stores, including those in Wuhan, Xi'an and other cities, are closed according to local government policies (supermarkets are open as usual) ; stores in other parts of the country have shortened their business hours, and allows the tenant to choose according to their own situation to continue business or apply for temporary closure.

Since February 10, work has resumed in all areas. However, large shopping malls to shorten business hours, the closure of these epidemic prevention measures continue.

Most of Shenzhen's shopping malls have adjusted their opening hours to 11:00-19:00. Only supermarkets extend their opening hours. "refuse to dine together" has even become part of the anti-epidemic slogans of shopping malls.

"although Shenzhen enterprises have resumed work, orders for both in-house and take-out food are still small, " a staff member at a Hong Kong tea restaurant at the Zhuo Yue Center told interface news

"from January 27 to February 9, our shopping malls were closed except for supermarkets and convenience stores, " said Huang Xiaojuan, manager of Dongguan Zhuoweicheng's planning department. February 10 after the resumption of work, the company's employees are also working in batches to meet daily operational needs. Only part of the shops are open, and the opening hours of all the shops have not yet been determined."

Knight Frank Expects A short-term slowdown in demand from retailers as a result of the epidemic, which will lead to a lack of demand from retailers for new shopping mall openings, as a result, it is more difficult to attract investment in the newly-built shopping center, and the owners have to offer more favorable terms.

Vacancy rates are expected to rise in some of the new malls, leading to slower deliveries and reduced market availability in some of the under-construction malls.

Knight Frank is also expecting some of its still-open retailers to offer more favourable terms for their leases, while negotiations over rental levels are under greater downward pressure.

In the long term, retailers are confident of continued spending power growth, and expect their expansion plans to continue after the epidemic is contained.

Naixue tea in the official said: 2020 we plan to open more stores, deeply tilling the second and third-tier cities. New Store openings are still being planned, with some delays in the first quarter due to the impact of the epidemic. We are always ready to jump into business as soon as the epidemic is over.

In the face of this sudden outbreak, commercial real estate operators and retailers are willing to help themselves. In the strict epidemic prevention work, waiting for the end of the "war epidemic" , looking forward to the day of heavy traffic and crowds.
